# 1. What is an HTML Form?

## Definition

An HTML Form is a section of a webpage that allows users to enter information and send it to the server for processing.

Forms are one of the most important parts of web applications because they collect user input.

---

## Real-Time Examples

Examples of HTML Forms:

- Login Form
- Registration Form
- Contact Form
- Online Banking Transfer Form
- Railway Ticket Booking Form
- College Admission Form
- Employee Salary Prediction Form

---

## Answer

An HTML Form is used to collect user input and send it to the server.

---

# 2. Why Do We Need HTML Forms?

Without forms,

Users cannot enter data into a website.

Our application needs information such as:

- Employee Name
- Age
- Education
- Experience
- Job Role

This information is entered using an HTML Form.

---

## Answer

HTML Forms allow users to provide data that can be processed by Flask and Machine Learning.

---

# 3. Form Elements

A form contains different input elements.

| Element | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| Text Box | Enter text |
| Number Box | Enter numbers |
| Dropdown | Select one option |
| Radio Button | Select one item |
| Checkbox | Select multiple items |
| Submit Button | Send data |

---

## Answer

Different form elements are used depending on the type of data the user enters.

