# 10. What is GET Method?

GET sends data through the URL.

Example

```text
http://localhost:5000/?name=Rahul
```

Advantages

- Easy to test
- Used for searching

Disadvantages

- Data is visible in the URL
- Not secure for sensitive information

---

## Answer

GET is used when the data is safe to appear in the URL.

---

# 11. What is POST Method?

POST sends data inside the request body.

Example

```html
<form method="POST">
```

Advantages

- Secure
- Large amount of data
- Passwords remain hidden

---

## Answer

POST is the preferred method for forms that send important information.

---

# 12. GET vs POST

| GET | POST |
|------|------|
| Data in URL | Data in Request Body |
| Less Secure | More Secure |
| Small Data | Large Data |
| Search Forms | Registration/Login Forms |

---

## Answer

Our Salary Prediction project will use the **POST** method.

---

# 13. Updating the Form to Use POST

Update the form tag.

```html
<form method="POST">
```

---

## Answer

Now the form sends data securely to Flask.

